  "text": "We can also define the equivalent of CRGs in this setting. In [10], the term type is used, though for consistency of this paper, we will just call them r-CRGs. [CITATION_1] Definition 38 An r-CRG K is a pair (U, φ ) where U is a finite set of vertices and φ : U × U → 2 {1,...,r} − / 0 such that φ (x, y) = φ (y, x) and φ (x, x) = {1, . . . , r}. The sub-r-CRG induced by W ⊆ U is the r-CRG that results from deleting U −W .",
