      "span_text": "In [10], the term type is used, though for consistency of this paper, we will just call them r-CRGs.  Definition 38 An r-CRG K is a pair (U, φ ) where U is a finite set of vertices and φ : U × U → 2 {1,...,r} − / 0 such that φ (x, y) = φ (y, x) and φ (x, x) = {1, . . . , r}."
